          'Router': 'A network device that connects different networks and forwards packets using IP addresses at Layer 3.',
          'Firewall': 'A security device that monitors and controls network traffic based on security rules.',
          'Wireless Access Point': 'A device that allows wireless devices to connect to a wired network using Wi-Fi.',
          'MAC Address': 'A unique hardware address used to identify devices on a local network at Layer 2.',
